## 7. Error Handling and Fallback Strategy

### 7.1 Ollama Unavailability

If the Ollama service is down or times out, the system falls back to the existing direct search path:

```typescript
async startConversation({ body }: { body: StartConversationDto }): Promise<ConversationResponseDto> {
  const conversationId = randomUUID();
  let analysis: ILlmAnalysisResult;

  try {
    analysis = await this.ollamaService.analyzeQuery({ query: body.q });
  } catch (error) {
    this.logger.warn(`Ollama analysis failed, falling back to direct search: ${(error as Error).message}`);
    const products = await this.opensearchNeuralService.searchProducts({
      queryText: body.q,
      ...(body.limit !== undefined && { size: body.limit }),
    });

    return {
      conversationId,
      needsClarification: false,
      searchResults: {
        query: body.q,
        total: products.length,
        products,
      },
    };
  }
  // ... normal flow
}
```

### 7.2 Malformed LLM Response

Llama 3B may produce invalid JSON. The `OllamaService.analyzeQuery()` method wraps `JSON.parse` in a try-catch and retries once. If it still fails, it throws a specific error that triggers the fallback above.

```typescript
private parseLlmResponse({ content }: { content: string }): ILlmAnalysisResult {
  const cleaned = content.replace(/```json\n?/g, '').replace(/```\n?/g, '').trim();
  const parsed = JSON.parse(cleaned) as ILlmAnalysisResult;

  if (typeof parsed.needsClarification !== 'boolean' || !parsed.analysis?.enhancedQuery) {
    throw new Error('Invalid LLM response structure');
  }

  return parsed;
}
```

### 7.3 Conversation Not Found (404)

When `continueConversation` is called with an expired or invalid `conversationId`, throw a `NotFoundException`:

```typescript
const state = await this.cacheService.get<IConversationState>({
  namespace: Namespaces.NEURAL_SEARCH_CONVERSATION,
  key: conversationId,
});
if (!state) {
  throw new NotFoundException('Conversation not found or expired');
}
```

### 7.4 OpenAI SDK Timeout

Configure the OpenAI client with a timeout to prevent the request from hanging if Ollama is unresponsive:

```typescript
this.client = new OpenAI({
  apiKey: 'ollama',
  baseURL,
  timeout: 15000, // 15 second timeout
  maxRetries: 1,
});
```

